CONFERENCE COMMITTEE REPORT DIGEST
SB 382 2026 Regular Session Seabaugh
Keyword and summary of the bill as proposed by the Conference Committee
WORKERS' COMPENSATION. Provides relative to workers' compensation. (8/1/26)
Report adopts House amendments to:
1. Amend provisions of present law that permit annual adjustments to the
reimbursement schedule.
Report rejects House amendments which would have:
1. Required the assistant secretary to reassess the reimbursement schedule and
promulgate and implement any necessary adjustments no later than January 1, 2027.
Report amends the bill to:
1. Require the assistant secretary to reassess the reimbursement schedule and
promulgate and implement any necessary adjustments no later than July 1, 2029.
Digest of the bill as proposed by the Conference Committee
Present law provides that the reimbursement schedule includes charges limited to the mean
of the usual and customary charges for care, services, treatment, drugs, and supplies. Present
law allows annual adjustments.
Proposed law retains present law and requires the assistant secretary to reassess the
reimbursement schedule and implement necessary adjustments to the schedule by July 1,
2029.
Present law creates the Workers' Compensation Advisory Council (council) within Louisiana
Works. Present law further provides that the council consists of 17 members who are
domiciled in Louisiana and appointed by the governor to serve at the pleasure of the
governor. Present law further provides relative to the duties of the council and members'
immunity from liability under certain circumstances.
Present law further requires the council to review and make recommendations to the
governor, through Louisiana Works, on any proposed rules affecting the administration or
resolution of claims.
Proposed law repeals present law.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Amends R.S. 23:1034.2(C)(1); repeals R.S. 23:1294 and R.S. 36:309(B)(2))

